# Error Handling and Logging Standards

This rule ensures consistent, type-safe error handling and logging across the entire Senate BE codebase. It enforces the use of proper error types, logging patterns, and parameter structures to maintain code quality and debugging capabilities.

## I. Error Handling Hierarchy

### 1. Base Error Classes (from `src/utils/errors.ts`)
Use these for simple domain errors without HTTP context:

```typescript
// Simple domain errors
import { 
  BaseError, 
  BadRequestError, 
  NotFoundError, 
  UnauthorizedError, 
  ForbiddenError, 
  ConflictError, 
  ValidationError 
} from "../utils/errors.js";

// Usage
throw new NotFoundError("Document not found");
throw new ForbiddenError("Access denied to this document");
throw new ValidationError("Invalid document format");
```

### 2. App Errors (from `src/middleware/errorHandler.ts`)
Use these for service-layer errors with HTTP status codes:

```typescript
import { 
  AppError, 
  DatabaseError, 
  AuthError, 
  NotFoundError, 
  ValidationError 
} from "../middleware/errorHandler.js";

// Usage with status codes and cause chaining
throw new AppError("Document processing failed", 500, { cause: originalError });
throw new DatabaseError("Connection to OCR database failed");
throw new ValidationError("Document metadata validation failed", { 
  title: "Title is required",
  content_type: "Invalid content type" 
});
```

### 3. HTTP Errors (from `src/utils/http-errors.ts`)
Use these for controller-layer errors with detailed HTTP responses:

```typescript
import { HttpError, errorTypes } from "../utils/http-errors.js";

// Usage in controllers
throw errorTypes.badRequest("Invalid document upload", { field: "file", reason: "unsupported_format" });
throw errorTypes.forbidden("Access denied to document", { documentId: docId, userId: user.id });
throw errorTypes.notFound("Document not found", { documentId: docId });
throw errorTypes.validation("Document validation failed", { errors: validationResults });
```

## II. Error Handling Patterns

### 1. Service Layer Error Handling
**REQUIRED**: Use `executeDbOperation` wrapper for all database operations:

```typescript
import { executeDbOperation, throwIfNotFound } from "../utils/errorUtils.js";
import { AppError, DatabaseError } from "../middleware/errorHandler.js";

// CORRECT - Document service example
async getDocumentById(id: string): Promise<DocumentModel> {
  return executeDbOperation(
    async () => {
      const document = await this.repository.findById(id);
      throwIfNotFound(document, "Document", id);
      return document;
    },
    "document",
    "getDocumentById"
  );
}

// CORRECT - OCR service example
async processDocument(documentId: string, filePath: string): Promise<void> {
  return executeDbOperation(
    async () => {
      await this.ocrRepository.updateProcessingStatus(documentId, {
        processing_status: ProcessingStatus.PROCESSING
      });
      
      const result = await this.documentAiService.processDocument(filePath);
      if (!result) {
        throw new AppError("Document AI processing failed", 500);
      }
      
      await this.ocrRepository.createOrUpdateExtractedText(documentId, {
        extracted_text: result.text,
        processing_status: ProcessingStatus.COMPLETED
      });
    },
    "document_ocr",
    "processDocument"
  );
}

// INCORRECT - No error wrapper
async getDocumentById(id: string): Promise<DocumentModel> {
  const document = await this.repository.findById(id);
  if (!document) throw new Error("Document not found"); // Wrong error type
  return document;
}
```

### 2. OCR and Document Processing Error Handling
**REQUIRED**: Use specific error patterns for OCR operations:

```typescript
// CORRECT - OCR service error handling
async extractTextFromDocument(documentId: string, filePath: string): Promise<OcrResult> {
  try {
    logger.info("Starting OCR processing", { documentId, filePath });
    
    const result = await this.geminiService.extractTextFromPdf(filePath);
    
    logger.info("OCR processing completed", { 
      documentId, 
      textLength: result.extractedText.length,
      pageCount: result.pageCount 
    });
    
    return result;
  } catch (error: unknown) {
    const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
    
    logger.error("OCR processing failed", error as Error, {
      documentId,
      filePath,
      errorType: typeof error
    });
    
    await this.ocrRepository.updateProcessingStatus(documentId, {
      processing_status: ProcessingStatus.ERROR,
      processing_error: errorMessage
    });
    
    throw new AppError(`OCR processing failed: ${errorMessage}`, 500, { cause: error });
  }
}
```

### 3. Authorization Error Handling
**REQUIRED**: Use specific authorization checks with proper error types:

```typescript
// CORRECT
async updateDocument(id: string, dto: UpdateDocumentDto, userId: string): Promise<DocumentModel> {
  const document = await this.getDocumentById(id);
  
  if (document.user_id !== userId && !(await this.userService.isAdmin(userId))) {
    logger.warn("Authorization denied for document update", {
      documentId: id,
      ownerId: document.user_id,
      requestingUserId: userId,
      operation: "updateDocument"
    });
    throw new ForbiddenError("You can only update your own documents");
  }
  
  return this.repository.update(id, dto, userId);
}

// INCORRECT
async updateDocument(id: string, dto: UpdateDocumentDto, userId: string): Promise<DocumentModel> {
  const document = await this.getDocumentById(id);
  if (document.user_id !== userId) {
    throw new Error("Not allowed"); // Generic error
  }
  return this.repository.update(id, dto, userId);
}
```

### 4. Controller Error Handling
**REQUIRED**: Use `asyncHandler` wrapper and proper HTTP error types:

```typescript
import { asyncHandler } from "../middleware/errorHandler.js";
import { errorTypes } from "../utils/http-errors.js";

// CORRECT
export const uploadDocument = asyncHandler(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {
  const { file } = req;
  const userId = req.user?.id;
  
  if (!file) {
    throw errorTypes.badRequest("File is required for document upload");
  }
  
  if (!userId) {
    throw errorTypes.unauthorized("User authentication required");
  }
  
  logger.info("Document upload initiated", {
    userId,
    fileName: file.originalname,
    fileSize: file.size,
    mimeType: file.mimetype
  });
  
  const result = await billLibraryService.uploadAndProcessDocument(file, req.body, userId);
  
  logger.info("Document upload completed", {
    userId,
    documentId: result.id,
    fileName: file.originalname
  });
  
  res.status(201).json({ success: true, data: result });
});

// INCORRECT - No asyncHandler wrapper
export const uploadDocument = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {
  try {
    const result = await billLibraryService.uploadAndProcessDocument(req.file, req.body, req.user.id);
    res.json(result);
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Upload failed" }); // Manual error handling
  }
};
```

## III. Logging Standards

### 1. Logger Initialization
**REQUIRED**: Create service-specific logger instances using the project's custom Logger:

```typescript
import { Logger } from "../utils/logger.js";

// CORRECT - Service-specific logger
const logger = new Logger({ serviceName: "BillLibraryService" });
const logger = new Logger({ serviceName: "OcrService" });
const logger = new Logger({ serviceName: "GeminiService" });
const logger = new Logger({ serviceName: "DocumentController" });

// INCORRECT - Generic or missing logger
const logger = console; // Don't use console directly
```

### 2. Logging Levels and Metadata

#### Debug Logging
```typescript
// CORRECT - Structured metadata for debugging
logger.debug("Processing document request", {
  documentId: document.id,
  operation: "uploadAndProcessDocument",
  userId: user.id,
  fileSize: file.size,
  mimeType: file.mimetype
});

// INCORRECT - String concatenation
logger.debug(`Processing document ${document.id} for user ${user.id}`);
```

#### Info Logging
```typescript
// CORRECT - Important business events
logger.info("Document OCR processing started", {
  documentId: document.id,
  engine: "GEMINI",
  filePath: document.file_path,
  userId: user.id,
  operationId: `ocr_${document.id}_${Date.now()}`
});

logger.info("Document processing completed", {
  documentId: document.id,
  processingStatus: ProcessingStatus.COMPLETED,
  textLength: extractedText.length,
  pageCount: result.pageCount,
  processingDuration: Date.now() - startTime
});
```

#### Warning Logging
```typescript
// CORRECT - OCR and service warnings
logger.warn("OCR processing timeout approaching", {
  documentId: document.id,
  engine: selectedEngine,
  elapsedTime: Date.now() - startTime,
  timeoutThreshold: PROCESSING_TIMEOUT
});

logger.warn("Gemini extraction truncated due to MAX_TOKENS", {
  documentId: document.id,
  gcsPdfPath: filePath,
  finishReason: "MAX_TOKENS",
  textLength: fullText.length,
  safetyRatings: response.candidates[0].safetyRatings
});

// INCORRECT - Direct error object without structure
logger.warn("Processing failed", error); // Error object not properly structured
```

#### Error Logging
```typescript
// CORRECT - Use logger.error with Error object and context
logger.error("Document AI processing failed", error as Error, {
  documentId: document.id,
  operationName: "batchProcessDocument",
  gcsInputPath: inputPath,
  outputPrefix: outputPrefix,
  attemptNumber: retryCount
});

logger.error("Database connection failed during OCR update", error as Error, {
  operation: "updateProcessingStatus",
  documentId: document.id,
  processingStatus: ProcessingStatus.ERROR,
  connectionPool: "ocr_repository"
});

// INCORRECT - Wrong parameter order or missing context
logger.error("Processing failed", { documentId: document.id }, error); // Wrong parameter order
logger.error("Error occurred", error as Error); // Missing business context
```

