## IV. Type Safety Requirements

### 1. Error Constructor Parameters
**REQUIRED**: Always provide proper types for error constructors:

```typescript
// CORRECT - Explicit types with cause chaining
throw new AppError("Document processing failed", 500, { cause: originalError });
throw new DatabaseError("OCR repository connection failed");
throw new ValidationError("Document metadata validation failed", {
  title: "Title is required",
  content_type: "Must be one of: BILL, RESOLUTION"
});

// INCORRECT - Missing or wrong types
throw new AppError("Error"); // Missing status code
throw new Error("Document not found"); // Wrong error class
```

### 2. Logger Metadata Types
**REQUIRED**: Use `Record<string, unknown>` for metadata:

```typescript
// CORRECT - Proper metadata typing
const ocrMetadata: Record<string, unknown> = {
  documentId: document.id,
  operation: "processDocumentOcr",
  engine: selectedEngine,
  filePath: document.file_path,
  userId: user.id,
  startTime: Date.now()
};
logger.info("OCR processing initiated", ocrMetadata);

// INCORRECT - Untyped metadata that may cause circular references
logger.info("Processing started", { document, request, user }); // Objects may contain circular references
```

### 3. Error Handling in Catch Blocks
**REQUIRED**: Properly type and handle unknown errors:

```typescript
// CORRECT - Proper error typing for OCR operations
try {
  await this.geminiService.extractTextFromPdf(gcsPdfPath);
} catch (error: unknown) {
  if (error instanceof AppError) {
    throw error; // Re-throw known errors
  }
  
  const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
  logger.error("Unexpected error in Gemini OCR processing", error as Error, {
    operation: "extractTextFromPdf",
    documentId: documentId,
    gcsPdfPath: gcsPdfPath,
    errorType: typeof error
  });
  
  // Update OCR status to ERROR
  await this.ocrRepository.updateProcessingStatus(documentId, {
    processing_status: ProcessingStatus.ERROR,
    processing_error: `GeminiOcrService: ${errorMessage}`
  });
  
  throw new AppError(`OCR processing failed: ${errorMessage}`, 500, { cause: error });
}

// INCORRECT - Untyped error handling
try {
  await this.processDocument();
} catch (error) { // Missing type annotation
  console.log(error); // Direct console usage
  throw error; // Re-throwing unknown error type
}
```

